# 📊 Telecom Customer Churn Analysis

## 📌 Objective
The goal of this project is to predict customer churn in the telecom industry and identify key factors influencing customer retention.

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies
- Python
- Pandas
- Scikit-learn
- Matplotlib

## 📂 Dataset
The dataset contains customer information such as usage patterns, services, and subscription details along with churn status.

## ⚙️ Methodology

1. Data Cleaning
   - Handled missing values
   - Verified churn column (already in 0/1 format)

2. Data Preprocessing
   - Converted categorical variables using one-hot encoding

3. Model Building
   - Logistic Regression model used for binary classification

4. Evaluation
   - Accuracy score
   - Classification report
   - Confusion matrix

## 📊 Key Insights

- Customers with shorter tenure are more likely to churn  
- High monthly charges increase churn probability  
- Customers with fewer subscribed services tend to leave  
- Long-term contracts significantly reduce churn  

## 💡 Business Recommendations

- Offer retention incentives for high-risk customers  
- Encourage long-term subscription plans  
- Improve customer service for better satisfaction  
- Target new users with onboarding benefits  

## 📈 Results

The model successfully predicts customer churn and helps identify key drivers behind customer behavior.

## 🚀 Conclusion

This project demonstrates how machine learning can be used to improve customer retention strategies in a competitive telecom environment.
